    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a mechanically robust 2011 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8 and a 6-speed longitudinal manual transmission. This high-revving unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure VANOS system to deliver linear power up to its 8,400 RPM redline. The chassis is equipped with Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and a variable M differential lock for precise corner-exit traction. Recent preventative maintenance includes the critical replacement of rod bearings and throttle actuators, ensuring the longevity of the valvetrain and bottom end. While the exterior displays minor road-derived patina, the structural integrity and suspension kinematics remain sharp, providing the tactile feedback expected of the M-division\u2019s hydraulic steering rack.",
